snippet.textDisplay:
Bet they sent these vehicles to the scrap yard.


Shock absorbers shot to pieces, interiors falling apart, oil leaks everywhere.


Most off-road vehicles can do this at least once in their lifetime, but they won't do it again without needing maintenance or repairs.

snippet.textDisplay:
The iconic Defender has come far and away from its humble yet useful beginnings, the new Defender has become a marketing gimmick, a puny crossover which is overweight, underpowered and it disrespects the legacy of the original Defender.

In my opinion, somehow, the Suzuki Jimney lives up to be the true heir of the Defender.
